abstract: What happens when hundreds of reporters from New York and Washington go to Des Moines? A sponsored Sunday brunch.
snippet: What happens when hundreds of reporters from New York and Washington go to Des Moines? A sponsored Sunday brunch.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Every spring, the Washington impresario Tammy Haddad hosts a charity brunch before the White House Correspondents’ Dinner that is a required stop for reporters, editors, network news anchors and political operatives.

abstract: “What we are demanding now is demonstrable evidence of their will and capacity to reduce violence,” Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said of the latest negotiations.
snippet: “What we are demanding now is demonstrable evidence of their will and capacity to reduce violence,” Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said of the latest negotiations.
lead_paragraph: TASHKENT, Uzbekistan — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said Monday that the Trump administration was moving ahead with peace talks with the Taliban to end the war in Afghanistan. But to reach a deal, he said, the Taliban must first  give “demonstrable evidence of their will and capacity to reduce violence.”

abstract: J. Lo wore a Puerto Rican flag. Children appeared in orbs that looked like cages. Beyoncé and Jay-Z sat during the national anthem. Were they all saying something?

lead_paragraph: Were Beyoncé and Jay-Z making a political statement when they sat during the national anthem? Was Jennifer Lopez alluding to President Trump’s immigration practices by having children sitting in cage-like orbs? What about that Puerto Rican flag?

headline_main: What Is Your Reaction to the Results of the Iowa Caucuses?

abstract: An annual watch party turned into a mini caucus, as longtime friends wrestled with choosing a Democratic candidate to support.
